						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in the field called Kāḍappanavara hola, about three miles from the village.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1351.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1273, Khara, Bhādrapad Paurṇami, Wednesday, Lunar eclipse.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1351, September 5,</hi> when the weekday was Tuesday. The eclipse did not occur on that day.</p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record a gift of land to god Sōmanātha of <hi rend="bold">Agrā[khēḍa].</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
